5.22.20  2:32 pm   How did you go about learning and teaching yourself new things?

     i'm still doing it

     How did you teach yourself music?

     music taught itself to me .... it's sort of like learning colors. it's not exactly like that, but it's like that in the sense that no one has to teach themself colors. they just look the way they look. then from there it's all fun and games and epic breakthroughs in the name of science

      I don't know where to start, but I would love to learn.

     i think the best way to go from here, is to trace back your desire. when you say you 'would love to' .... 2 questions come to mind, 1 is what exactly is the thing you would love to do, but there's no point in answering that until you answer the other question, which was do you remember how and when you encountered this desire. once you remember that, you will actually find all the other answers there

5.22.20  10:14 am   i sent someone some art that i made for them. they have not responded and it is making me feel truly awful. i feel like it was a silly thing to do even though i thought it was cool when i did it. i know they may not have even seen it yet but my brain can't help but assume the worst, maybe i'm just being insecure and i shouldn't take it so personally. however i cannot stop thinking about how ashamed i feel for doing it. which sounds insane because its just art, and it really isn't that big of a deal but i can't stop obsessing over why they haven't responded. do they not like it? do they think it's weird that i made it for them? i wish i could unsend it. sorry that i sound like a crazy person. i think i may have truly lost the plot. if you have any advice for how i can get over this absurdness or any advice at all, it would be greatly appreciated. 

      make sure you do a lot of writing, and creating. and be aware of the supercharged thinkfactory that is your mind, try to use it as a creative tool, and not be too alarmed at the side-order of somewhat predictably frequent storms
